# Witt — Environment Variable Reference

Copy `.env.example` to `.env.dev`, `.env.staging`, `.env.prod` and fill in real values.
Never commit `.env.*` files (they are gitignored). Only `.env.example` is committed.

## Required Variables

| Variable              | Description                                              | Where to get it                                      |
|-----------------------|----------------------------------------------------------|------------------------------------------------------|
| SUPABASE_URL          | Supabase project REST API URL                            | Supabase Dashboard → Project Settings → API          |
| SUPABASE_ANON_KEY     | Supabase anon/publishable key (safe for client-side)     | Supabase Dashboard → Project Settings → API          |
| ONESIGNAL_APP_ID      | OneSignal App ID for push notifications (all platforms)  | OneSignal Dashboard → App → Keys & IDs               |
| SENTRY_DSN            | Sentry Data Source Name for error tracking               | Sentry Dashboard → Project → Settings → Client Keys  |
| MIXPANEL_TOKEN        | Mixpanel project token for analytics                     | Mixpanel Dashboard → Project Settings → Access Keys  |

## Optional Variables (AI — used in Phase 3)

| Variable              | Description                                              | Where to get it                                      |
|-----------------------|----------------------------------------------------------|------------------------------------------------------|
| GROQ_API_KEY          | Groq API key (free-tier AI, non-exam features)           | console.groq.com → API Keys                          |
| OPENAI_API_KEY        | OpenAI API key (paid-tier AI, non-exam features)         | platform.openai.com → API Keys                       |
| CLAUDE_API_KEY        | Anthropic Claude API key (exam question generation only) | console.anthropic.com → API Keys                     |
| SUBRAIL_API_KEY       | Subrail billing SDK API key (purchase flows)             | Subrail Dashboard → Project Settings → API Keys      |

## SDK Activation Notes

- **Sentry**: SDK initializes only if `SENTRY_DSN` is non-empty. Safe to leave blank in dev.
- **Mixpanel**: SDK initializes only if `MIXPANEL_TOKEN` is non-empty. Tracks `app_open` on launch.
- **OneSignal**: SDK initializes only if `ONESIGNAL_APP_ID` is non-empty. Requests notification permission on first launch.
- **Supabase**: Required in all environments. App will crash on launch if missing.
- **Subrail**: SDK initializes only if `SUBRAIL_API_KEY` is non-empty. Purchase flows fall back to error state if missing. Uses sandbox mode in debug builds automatically.

## Auth Providers (Supabase Dashboard)

Configure in Supabase Dashboard → Authentication → Providers:
- Email/Password — enabled by default
- Google OAuth — requires `GOOGLE_CLIENT_ID` + `GOOGLE_CLIENT_SECRET` in Supabase dashboard
- Apple OAuth — requires Apple Developer credentials in Supabase dashboard
- Phone OTP — requires a Twilio / MessageBird account configured in Supabase dashboard
- Anonymous — enable toggle in Supabase Dashboard → Authentication → Providers → Anonymous

